## 7. Failure modes & blast radius

| Trigger | Consequence | Mitigation and recovery |
|---|---|---|
| Phase 2 runs before Phase 1 | Dishonest semantics become normalized. | Hard ancestry/digest precondition and semantic epochs. |
| Collector assumes fictional paths | Real attempts become all-error. | Only concrete artifact or PLAN-003-defined pointers may be mandatory. |
| PLAN-003 schema changes after pin | Extraction semantics drift. | Verify schema and extractor digests before collection. |
| Phase 2 and `metrics_report.py` disagree | Conflicting terminal/gate metrics. | Reuse extractor or require fixture-equivalence tests. |
| Historical v3 is coerced to v4 | False structured findings and severities. | Display-only historical epoch; no v4 comparison. |
| Reviewer finding is treated as disposition | Reviewer assertion becomes operator fact. | Separate event/table types linked by finding identity. |
| Missing result is ignored | Interrupted/orphan attempts disappear. | Inventory snapshot and incomplete coverage report. |
| Collector bug misreads a field | Incorrect report fact. | Exact pointers, provenance, schemas, source digest, and schema-version correction. |
| Duplicate collection | Inflated counts. | Deterministic IDs, lock, unique constraint. |
| Two collectors race | Interleaved lines. | Exclusive `flock` and append under lock. |
| Process dies during append | Partial final line. | Next collection refuses append; preserve corrupt copy before manual trailing-byte repair. |
| Ledger is corrupted mid-file | Projection is untrusted. | Stop with exit 2; restore or reconstruct at a new path. |
| Source mutates during read | Digest/payload mismatch. | `lstat`/`fstat` checks. |
| Evidence contains traversal/symlink | Out-of-scope read. | Relative normalization, no `..`, reject symlinks. |
| Evidence contains HTML/JS | Local report execution. | Strict escaping and malicious-fixture tests. |
| Token field disappears | False cost reduction. | `null` plus unknown coverage. |
| Cached tokens are double-counted | Inflated cost. | Cached input remains a subset of total input. |
| Item records lack tool names | Tool use is fabricated. | Classify only from real `/item/type`; unsupported details remain null. |
| Capture write fails | Missing capture data. | Best-effort capture and explicit coverage. |
| Reviewer wrapper changes dispatch behavior | Verdict or timeout regression. | `P2-02` owns call-site diff; equivalence and fault-injection tests. |
| Capture code changes ordering | Gate/verdict regression. | Isolated high-assurance spec and normalized evidence comparison. |
| PID unavailable | Incomplete process detail. | PID nullable; invocation ID/systemd unit remain identity. |
| Invocation lacks finish/join | Duration/concurrency cannot close. | Incomplete coverage; no inferred zero. |
| Git object is pruned | Diff unavailable. | `git_object_missing`; retain other attempt facts. |
| PR evidence absent | Merge details unavailable. | Nullable coverage; use only real `/merged`, `/merged_via`, `/pr_url`. |
| SQLite build fails | Report stale or absent. | Atomic temporary build; ledger intact. |
| Report build fails | No updated dashboard. | Preserve old report and rebuild later. |
| Golden hidden data leaks | Benchmark invalid. | Separate hidden files and version dataset after leak. |
| Fixture commit changes | Runs incomparable. | Digest verification. |
| Golden run touches production | Production side effect. | Fixture-only repos, no remotes, PR disabled. |
| Reviewer-value fixtures drift | Audit/golden disagreement. | One manifest source and digest tests. |
| Full matrix launched accidentally | Excess quota/confounding. | Pairwise default and explicit authorization. |
| Harness overfits visible tasks | Misleading gains. | Holdouts, hidden checks, versioned changes. |
| Composite score is added | Safety regression concealed. | Schema/report rejection tests. |
| Measurement influences gates | New trust surface. | Static dependency and runtime path canaries. |
| Comparison crosses semantic epochs | Invalid A/B conclusion. | Require identical epoch and dataset version. |
| Baseline has few repeats | Overstated certainty. | Display distributions and directional claims. |
| Finding ID collision | Wrong adjudication link. | Digest-derived IDs and source verification. |

Worst credible Phase 2 failure is a misleading report that drives a poor operator decision. It cannot directly approve, reject, merge, or alter an attempt. The only trust-critical code risk is capture integration in `scripts/dispatch.py`; its blast radius is bounded by high-assurance review, per-dispatch approval, fault injection, and independent rollback.

